<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/967> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #967" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under Rullianus in Samnium (Liv. 10.14.10). See Münzer, Gent. Val. 50, no. 50." ;
	dprr:hasID 967 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/912> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #912" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 9.43.25-26; 10.1.9; Fast. Cap. (names entire); Val. Max. 2.9.2; Degrassi 38f., 110, 422f. Brutus let contracts for building the temple of Salus, and for roads (Liv.; cf. on Salus, Grueber, CRRBM 1.248f.; Cesano, Stud. Num. 1.154f.). On Valerius, see Münzer, Gent. Val. 50, no. 50." ;
	dprr:hasID 912 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/883> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #883" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 9.28.8; Diod. 19.105.1; Fast. Cap. (names entire); Frontin. Aq. 1.5; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Degrassi 36f., 110, 420f. Decius was ill and remained in Rome (Liv. 9.29.3; cf. Auct. Vir. Ill. 27, a triumph over Samnites, not otherwise attested), but Valerius defeated the Samnites (Liv. 9.29.3), and, according to Act. Tr., celebrated a triumph over Samnites and Sorani (Degrassi 70f., 542). Diod. (19.105.5) mentions an attack on Pollitia of the Marrucini. On Valerius, see Münzer, Gent. Val. 50, no. 50." ;
	dprr:hasID 883 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/813> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #813" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Left in charge of the camp by the Dictator (Liv. 8.35.10-11). See Münzer, Gent. Val. 50, no. 50; and 49, no. 49." ;
	dprr:hasID 813 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/812> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #812" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Probably to be identified with the son of Corvus, Cos. 312, but may be the man of many consulships himself." ;
	dprr:hasID 812 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10241> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10241" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Samnitibus, Soraneisque. MRR I.159, Itgenshorst no. 79, Rich no. 79." ;
	dprr:hasID 10241 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1022> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1022" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Chr. 354 (Corvino II et Noctua); Fast. Hyd. (Maximo et Noctuo); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; Degrassi 112, 428f. On Valerius, see Lübker 50, no. 50." ;
	dprr:hasID 1022 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1021> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1021" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the name of Valerius, see Fast. Cap. on 312 and 307; on that of Caedicius, see Fast. Cap. on 283 and the filiation of his son, the Consul of 256. In Chr. Pasc. Caedicius has been confused with Decius Mus." ;
	dprr:hasID 1021 .
